LEGIONELLOSIS - SPAIN (02): (CATALONIA) FATAL, UPDATE, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
******************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Tue 23 Sep 2014
Source: 20minutos.es [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JG, edited]
http://www.20minutos.es/noticia/2246142/0/brote-legionela/siete-muertos/sabadell-ripollet/


The Generalitat (local autonomous government authority) detected a legionellosis outbreak in Ripollet (Barcelona) that has affected 5 persons, 3 of whom died, 1 is still hospitalized, and 1 has already been discharged from the hospital. A concurrent outbreak, which was detected 9 days ago, occurred in Sabadell (Barcelona), and has affected 34 persons, most of them elderly. 4 of these patients died and 17 are still hospitalized. The Ripollet outbreak was not reported until now because the affected individuals were admitted to distant hospitals, such as Calella and Hospital Del Mar Hospital in Barcelona.

This latest occurrence was announced last Tuesday [23 Sep 2014] in a press conference by the Secretary of the Public Health Agency of Catalonia, Mr Antoni Mateu, together with Mr Juan Parralejo, Mayor of Ripollet, and Ms Mireia Jane, Vice-Director of the Surveillance and Emergency Response in the Public Health Agency.

