[ProMED-mail previously reported this outbreak of legionnaires' disease in the Comarca (county) of Valles Occidental that had at time involved 23 cases, including 2 fatalities, in 3 towns north of Barcelona (ProMED-mail post Legionellosis - Spain: (CT) fatal 20140919.2788763); 20 of these 23 cases live in the city of Sabadell, 2 in the town of Barbera del Valles, and 1 in the town of Cerdanyola del Valles (Valles Occidental). The 1st news report above adds 11 more cases and the 2nd news report adds 4 more deaths for a total of 34 cases, including 8 deaths in these 3 towns.

In addition, the news reports above add another adjacent town (Ripollet) with 5 cases, including 3 deaths. Ripollet is a municipality of 29 877 residents in Valles Occidental in Catalonia located between Barbera del Valles and Cerdanyola (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ripollet). The 2nd news report says, "The proximity of the two towns raised suspicions that the cases of legionnaires' were linked but this possibility has since been ruled out, a health department official told AFP." ProMED-mail would appreciate more information from knowledgeable sources about how the Ripollet cases of legionnaires' disease differ from those in Sabadell, Barbera del Valles and Cerdanyola?

The prior news report said that 21 facilities with 38 cooling towers had been analyzed for _Legionella_ and remediated. Although samples were taken from these towers at the time, the news report above does not reveal the results of any microbiological testing.

Genotyping of patient and environmental _Legionella_ isolates may aid in establishing transmission pathways. The predominance of one genotype of _Legionella_ isolated from patient specimens would suggest transmission from a common source. Because _Legionella_ may be found in environmental samples without linkage to any cases of legionellosis, the actual causative infectious reservoir can be confirmed by matching the genotype of clinical and environmental isolates (see http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC86783/ and http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2730281/). However, this is often difficult in legionellosis outbreaks, because the diagnosis of legionnaires' disease is frequently made only on the basis of urinary _Legionella pneumophila_ serogroup 1 antigen testing or serology, rather than isolation of the organism from cultures of respiratory tract specimens. Consequently, clinical isolates are often not available for genotyping.

Maps of Spain can be seen at http://spain.europemaps.info/spain_map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2806305,41644.
Sabadell is the 2nd largest city, with a population of 207 938 people, in the southern portion of the Comarca of Valles Occidental, in Catalonia, Spain, 20 km (12 mi) north of Barcelona (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabadell). (A comarca is roughly equivalent to a US "county.") Barbera del Valles is a city of 29 208 people in Valles Occidental, 3 km (1.9 mi) south of Sabadell (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barberà_del_Vallès). Cerdanyola del Valles is a city of 58 747 people in Valles Occidental, 4.4 km (2.7 mi) south of Barbera del Valles (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerdanyola_del_Vallès).

A map of the cities of Valles Occidental can be found at http://www.idealista.com/venta-viviendas/barcelona/valles-occidental/mapa. A map of the comarcas of Catalonia can be found at http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/96/Catalunya%2BComarques%2BEnglish.jpg. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2806305,41864.]
